      "span_text": "Systemic corticosteroids are a fundamental therapeutic tool for active GO, and their use is associated with interference in the formation of ROS or an effect on ROS scavenging enzymes. Among the various types of oxidative damage in cellular structures or biomolecules induced by ROS, 8-hydroxy-2Ј-deoxyguanosine (8-OHdG) is one of the most abundant oxidative products of DNA and represents a noninvasive and sensitive biomarker of oxidative stress."
